      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>day in and day out!<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-289" title="chicken" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/chicken-300x260.jpg" alt="chicken" width="300" height="260" /></p>
<p>Aren&#8217;t you?</p>
<p>I happened to be complaining about this today, when hubs says to me, &#8220;Hey, that sounds like a blog post!  Get typing!&#8221;</p>
<p>So here I am&#8230;.typing about how sick and tired I am of eating the same foods, day in and day out.  When you go off plan, there seems to be so much more variety.  Right?  Sure, but it&#8217;s all stuff we shouldn&#8217;t be eating in the first place.</p>
<p>Here is what gets me, I have a great imagination.  I am very creative.  But at the end of the day, the very last thing I want to do is cook!  For the most part I like cooking.  But only when I don&#8217;t have to.  Getting creative with my food isn&#8217;t usually something I want to be bothered with at 5:30 when I&#8217;m hungry and everyone around me is hungry.</p>
<p>I swear if I eat any more chicken I&#8217;m going to sprout feathers and start clucking!</p>
<p>I&#8217;m totally burned out on broccoli!  I like it, but I just don&#8217;t want it anymore.  I&#8217;ve actually started eating asparagus, which is extremely rare for me.  Its good, but up until about a year ago I didn&#8217;t really know how to cook it.  I&#8217;m learning.</p>
<p>I also know that planning my food, and eating on a schedule and eating what I have planned is key to my success.  But life gets in my way.  As well as my own self&#8230;getting out of my own way is also an issue.</p>
<p>Ok&#8230;so we all agree I have issues! lol</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve said it before and I&#8217;ll say it again&#8230;.I need a wife!  Or maybe a chef training intern, who can come to my house and cook for us.  Oh, how cool would that be!?!?!!!!!!!</p>
<p>Some thoughts&#8230;.</p>
<ul>
<li>should a food addict be thinking about food all the time?</li>
<li>should a sugar addict be scouring recipe books?</li>
<li>should a food addict be searching thru food magazines looking for new foods to eat?</li>
</ul>
<p>I am tired of planning food, I am tired of cooking food, but I never tire of eating food.</p>
<p>It is always a wonderful day when hubs says, lets eat out, or he just takes over the cooking.  Because he doesn&#8217;t particularly like to cook, and I&#8217;m so tired of it and all the same foods, we have been eating out alot more.  Not such a good plan.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m a work in progress!</p>
<p>If anyone has any great suggestions for food prep, please leave a comment on how you do it!  I&#8217;d love to hear from you!</p>
