      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-242" title="Stack of chocolate cakes covered with chocolate sauce." src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/drippy-brownie-200x300.jpg" alt="Stack of chocolate cakes covered with chocolate sauce." width="200" height="300" /></h1>
<h1>It Hasn&#8217;t Been Easy</h1>
<p>.</p>
<p>But nobody said it would be did they?</p>
<p>I have been mia from posting here for a month.  A bit too long!  To add to my irritation, I just heard a friend has lost 40lbs in 2 weeks!  Yes you read that right&#8230;.but she also had lap band surgery 2 weeks ago.</p>
<p>It just kind of put a downer on me.</p>
<p>Where would I be today if I had kept at it.  I&#8217;d be 4 more weeks into this, and down a few more pounds.  Most definitely not 40, but a few.</p>
<p>Alright, well enough about that!</p>
<p>What has been happening around here.  First things got crazy busy in the shop, and that put my posting on hold.  Then because it got crazy busy, I let the stress get to me.  This is where I fall face first into the wine/chocolate/you name it!</p>
<p>Do I use food to relieve my stress?  Yes I do.  Why?  Because it actually makes me feel better.  I have really thought about this.  There are folks out there that say, its just this or that, and it&#8217;s a false feeling of peace when you eat yada yada yada.  So how do you explain the feeling of peace, and almost instant relaxation when I do?  Yes it lasts!  This is usually another argument.  That it will only last as long as it takes to eat it, or it will only last for another hour after I&#8217;ve eaten it.  No&#8230;I&#8217;m good for the night!  Ready to start the day again in the morning&#8230;.where the cycle starts all over.</p>
<p>Alright, so I got stressed out and I ate.  I got over it&#8230;then what happened?</p>
<p>I was at a vendor market and took a pretty bad fall that ended up needing chiropractic work, and massages to work out the pain.  That worked, but by this time I was so deeply ingrossed in my addictive behaviour that I didn&#8217;t even bother trying to come up for air.</p>
<p>I start thinking more &#8220;Beck&#8221; like and I start to pull myself back together, then&#8230;..</p>
<p>I end up in the emergency room after eating some sort of nut.  I took it easy the next 2 days after this, but food hasn&#8217;t been good.</p>
<p>I get going very good during the day, but the evenings have me fuddled.  Yes I understand I have a sugar sensitivity. I understand that it isn&#8217;t just a lack of willpower.  But sometimes it sure feels that way.  I&#8217;ve even tried to stay away from the tv, and to keep myself busy.  I s&#8217;pose I just need to fill my time a bit more.  It&#8217;s nice to just rest too.</p>
<p>Then what?  There couldn&#8217;t possibly be more right!?  We had our new grandbaby born into the family.  A little bit of heaven mixed in with all the stress and addictions!  She is beautiful and perfect!</p>
<p>It is going to feel wonderful to get back to &#8220;Sane Eating&#8221;.</p>
