      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&#8230;or most.  How ever they want to word it.</p>
<p>This topic was spurned on by a comment made to me by someone on twitter.  Pretty much telling me that sugar has gotten a bad rap, I need to eat it in moderation, etc. etc. etc.</p>
<p>Yah&#8230;Ok&#8230;.has he/she lived thru the friggin cravings that make your mind go crazy with the need to get a fix of sugar?!?  No I&#8217;m thinking they haven&#8217;t had to deal with it.</p>
<p>One size does <strong>NOT</strong> fit all!</p>
<p>Just like one diet does not work for everyone!</p>
<p>So let me ask this?  If I am dealing with an alcoholic, would I tell that person that alcohol has gotten a bad rap?  That it&#8217;s ok to drink, just drink wisely.</p>
<p><strong>No</strong></p>
<p>My blog and my twitter profile pretty much sum it up.  I am a sugar and food addict.  I cannot stop eating.  But alcoholics can stop drinking. I can stop eating sugar, but too often sugar gets put into things I do not suspect.  This often starts the cravings right back up.  As well as other foods that will sometimes trigger cravings, like bread, wine, potatoes, salad dressings etc.  Sugar is everywhere.  For those of us who cannot deal with it&#8230;.it is a big deal!</p>
<p>While I&#8217;m on a rant&#8230;.I&#8217;d like to discuss something else.</p>
<p>Nuts!</p>
<p>If you are allergic to nuts you will understand where I&#8217;m coming from.  If you are NOT allergic to nuts please keep reading, because you need to understand just how dangerous this is.</p>
<p>I was at an event last week.  I thought i made good choices.  15 minutes later, I was starting to have nut allergy symptoms.  I still cannot tell you where the nuts where.  Usually as soon as I have a nut in my mouth, it starts to bubble up and my throat starts to swell.  Every time in the past I have been able to get the nuts out of my mouth, drink lots of water and I&#8217;m uncomfortable for a while, but I&#8217;m ok.</p>
<p>Not this time!</p>
<p>I ended up in the hospital via an ambulance.  I can tell you I scared the hell out of my husband, myself and many of the neighbours who were on the sidewalk at 1:30 in the morning.</p>
<p>When you are going to an event and you are asked to bring a dish, either check to see if anyone is allergic to nuts or leave them OUT!</p>
<p>Nuts include the actual nut meat, nut oils or nut flours.  Its all nuts!  We react the same way.  However some of us react later when the nuts are well hidden in the ingredients&#8230;such as flours or oils.  Only this time it was alot more dangerous!  And No, we cannot eat around them!</p>
<p>Putting an ingredient in food that could be potentially deadly is careless and down right stupid!  Keep that stuff for who you know!</p>
