      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Michelle" href="http://www.healthandfitsolutions.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-214" title="healthfiness_solutions_logo_21" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/healthfiness_solutions_logo_21-300x159.jpg" alt="healthfiness_solutions_logo_21" width="300" height="159" /></a>This was suppose to be week 4 workouts, but life happens.  So Ive just renamed it #4.<br />
Home Exercise Program for:  Robin</p>
<p><strong>Squat Row</strong></p>
<p>Load the cable column machine with 45lbs and put the rope attachment on the lower cable.  Hold onto the rope with both hands with your arms extended.  Squat down, then stand and pull the rope up to your chest as you pull your shoulder blades together.  Hold this position for 1 second, then slowly release.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</p>
<p><strong>Lat Pull Down</strong></p>
<p>On the lat pull down machine, sit facing the weight stack and place your hands slight greater than shoulder width apart (and just past the bend of the bar).  Load the machined with 45lbs.  Exhale and pull the bar down to your chest by lower your elbows, inhale and slowly release the bar, making sure to pull your shoulder blades down toward your back pocket (ensuring your shoulders do not come up).</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</p>
<p><strong>Single Snatch</strong></p>
<p>Hold onto an 8lb dumbbell with your R hand, with your arm extended, and your palm facing back.  Squat down, and as you stand, lift the dumbbell up to your R shoulder making sure to keep the dumbbell close to your body.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12, and then alternate.</p>
<p><strong>Shoulder Fly</strong></p>
<p>Stand with your feet staggered.  The forward knee bent, and on your hind toes.  Bend your elbow slightly, and hold a 5lb dumbbell in each hand with each facing one another.  Open your arms and squeeze your shoulder blades together.</p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x’s 15.</p>
<p><strong>Serve</strong></p>
<p>Stand in a squat position with your feet about hips width apart and your knees supple.  Hold onto 5lb dumbbells in each hand, with your palms facing up.  With your elbows slightly bent, raise them up to shoulder height.  Hold for 1 second, then slowly release and return to your starting position.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</p>
<p><strong>Ball Crunches</strong></p>
<p>Sit on the large ball, and roll forward until it is on the small of your back.  Place your hands behind your head, and crunch up with your chin up toward the ceiling.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</p>
<p><strong>Oblique Crunches</strong></p>
<p>Assume the same position as the above ball crunches.  Crunch up and twist bring your R shoulder up and over.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12, and then alternate. (On each side).</p>
<p><strong>Dead Lift</strong></p>
<p>Stand with your feet about hips width apart, holding onto 8lb dumbbells in each hand.  Bend forward at your hips with your knees slightly, your back flat and your head up as deep as you are able with your back flat.  Hold for 1 second, and then slowly return to your starting position.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</p>
<p><strong>Cable Column Pull Down</strong></p>
<p>Load the cable column machine with 65lbs, and put the A attachment onto the top cable.  Grab onto the attachment with hands, squat down and lean back, pulling your navel to your back to engage your abs for support and balance.  Pull the cable to your chest as you pull your elbows to your side.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x’s 15.</p>
<p><strong>Machine Triceps Extension with a Rope</strong><br />
Load the cable column machine with 40lbs, and attach the rope extension onto the top cable.  Stand with your feet hips width apart, your elbows tucked into your side, exhale, and pull the rope down and out.  Slowly return your the rope to your starting position.<br />
Repeat for 2 x’s 12.</p>
