Similar Posts from Food and Sugar Addiction:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/week-2-workouts/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Week 2 Workouts'&gt;Week 2 Workouts&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;  Home Exercise Program for: Robin  Pile&amp;#8217; Squat   Stand...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/workout-4/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Workout #4'&gt;Workout #4&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;This was suppose to be week 4 workouts, but life...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/week-workout/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Week One Workout'&gt;Week One Workout&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;Health and Fit Solutions.com      Home Exercise Program for: Robin  ...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/food-and-sugar-addiction/Food_and_Sugar_Addiction-Week_3_Workout.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Michelle Mullen" href="http://www.healthandfitsolutions.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-214" title="healthfiness_solutions_logo_21" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/healthfiness_solutions_logo_21-300x159.jpg" alt="healthfiness_solutions_logo_21" width="300" height="159" /></a></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Home Exercise Program for:  </strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Robin</span></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Wall Squat</span></strong></p>
<p>Place a large ball against the wall, and stand with it on the small of your back.  Squat down, like you are sitting down on a chair with your feet forward and hips width apart. </p>
<p>Squat until your hips and knees are at a 90° angle, hold for 1 second, then push your weight through your heels and stand.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Pile&#8217; Squat</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Stand in the same position as the wall squat, only with your toes pointed out, and your heels forward.  Squat down until your knees and your hips are at the same level, hold for 1 second, then push your weight through your heels and stand to your starting position.  </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Chest Press Machine</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p>Sit on a chest press machine and load the machine with 25lbs and position the handles of the machine so that it is perpendicular to your shoulders.  Keeping your back flat, exhale and push the bar away from your chest.  Slowly lower down to starting position. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Chest Fly</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Sit on a chest fly machine; the one where your elbows are bent up against a pad and you have to squeeze them together, with your back flat against the seat.  Load the machine with 20bls, and squeeze your shoulders together.  Slowly open your arms as far as you are comfortable, then repeat. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br />
</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Wood Chop with Lunge</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Put the handle attachment to the top of a cable column, load the cable column with 30lbs, and then stand with your R hip next to it.  Get into a lunged position with your R foot behind you, while holding onto the handle attachment.  Extend both of your arms, then slowly pull the cable across your body, in a arch toward your L hip; be sure to bend at your waist, not just at your shoulders.  Hold for 1 second, then slowly reverse and return to your starting position. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12, and then alternate</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Machine Seated Row</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p>Sit on a seated row machine, with your chest pressed up against the pad.  Load the machine with 40lbs, sit tall, with your shoulders up, pull the bar/handles to your chest (under your bust) while squeezing your shoulder blades together.  Hold for 1 second, and slowly release.    </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Sunshine</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p>Stand with your feet about hips width apart, holding onto an 8lb dumbbell or a 9lb medicine ball (which ever you have) with both of your hands.  Keeping your arms slightly bent, slowly raise the weight over your head, hold for 1 second, and then slowly lower down to your hips. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 10</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Seated Leg Extension Machine</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Sit on the quad (thigh) extension machine in a position where your knees are in line with the joint that extends (it should be on the side of your knees).  With 20lbs, extend your legs to 85° (not fully extended), making sure to sit deep so that your butt does not come off the seat.  Slowly lower them down to your starting position. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12 </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br />
</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Hamstring Curl Machine (Sitting upright)</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Sit on a hamstring curl machine (the one where you sit up, not the one where you lie on your stomach).  Load the machine with 20 lbs.  Exhale and slowly bring your heels toward your butt.  Hold for 1 second, then slowly release. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Skull Crusher</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p>Lie on your back, holding a 3lb dumbbell in each hand, raise your arms in front of you.  Bend your elbows back toward your head, brining the weights by your ears.  Push up to the starting position, and repeat.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12</p>
<p> </p>
<p> I was told Ive graduated to 3 sets! lol</p>
