Similar Posts from Food and Sugar Addiction:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/week-3-workout/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Week 3 Workout!'&gt;Week 3 Workout!&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;   Home Exercise Program for:  Robin   Wall Squat...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/workout-4/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Workout #4'&gt;Workout #4&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;This was suppose to be week 4 workouts, but life...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/weekly-workouts/week-workout/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Week One Workout'&gt;Week One Workout&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;Health and Fit Solutions.com      Home Exercise Program for: Robin  ...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/food-and-sugar-addiction/Food_and_Sugar_Addiction-Week_2_Workouts.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong> <a href="http://www.healthandfitsolutions.com" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-203" title="healthfiness_solutions_logo_2" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/healthfiness_solutions_logo_2-300x159.jpg" alt="healthfiness_solutions_logo_2" width="300" height="159" /></a></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/healthfiness_solutions_logo_2.jpg"></a></strong><strong>Home Exercise Program for: </strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Robin</span></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Pile&#8217; <a class="zem_slink" title="Squat (exercise)" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squat_%28exercise%29">Squat</a></span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Stand with your feet about hips width apart and your toes pointed out and your heels forward.  Squat down until your knees and your hips are at the same level, hold for 1 second, then push your weight through your heels and stand to your starting position.  </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x&#8217;s 15</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Push-up</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Lower the bar to a squat machine so that it is level with your hips.  Place your hands on the bar so that your elbows and shoulders are perpendicular to each other.  Step back so that your chest leans down, lower your hips forward, lift your heels and lower your chest and hips down toward the bar.  Hold the <a class="zem_slink" title="Press-up" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Press-up">push-up</a> for 1 second, exhale and push your chest up and off the bar. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">45° Backward Lunge</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Begin with your feet about hips width apart.  Step <a class="zem_slink" title="Relative direction" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relative_direction">backward</a> 45° with your Right <a class="zem_slink" title="Foot" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foot">foot</a>, making sure to keep your Left foot still.  Squat back, pushing your hips down toward the ground.  Hold for 1 second, and then return to your starting position.  Repeat with your Right side 15x&#8217;s, then alternate with your Left.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 15.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Lat Pull Down</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>On the lat pull down machine, sit facing the weight <a class="zem_slink" title="Stack (data structure)" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_%28data_structure%29">stack</a> and place your hands slight greater than shoulder width apart (and just past the bend of the bar).  Load the machine with 40lbs.  Exhale and pull the bar down to your chest by lower your elbows, inhale and slowly release the bar, making sure to pull your <a class="zem_slink" title="Scapula" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scapula">shoulder blades</a> down toward your back pocket (ensuring your shoulders do not come up). </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Military Press</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Stand in a squat position with your shoulders in an up away from your body, and your elbows at shoulder height.  Begin with your palms and forearms turned in toward your head (palms facing each other), holding 3 lb weights.  Push the weights up and in over your head.  Slowly lower your elbows back to shoulder height.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x&#8217;s 10.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Hip Abduction Machine</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Sit on the hip abduction machine (machine that you separate your legs), and bring the pads as close together as you are able.  Load the machine with 30 lbs.  Slowly and in a controlled manner, separate your legs, then slowly release and bring them back together.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Hip Adduction Machine</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Sit on the hip <a class="zem_slink" title="Adduction" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adduction">adduction</a> machine (machine that you bring your legs together), and position the pads as far apart as you are able.  Load the machine with 35 lbs.  Slowly squeeze your legs together, and slowly release to and return to your starting position.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Biceps Curl</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Stand with your feet about hips width apart and soft knees.  Hold 5 lbs in each hand, with your palms forward.  Press your elbows into your stomach; bend your elbows to your shoulders. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Machine Triceps Extension with a Bar</span></strong></p>
<p>Load the cable column machine with 30lbs, and attach the bar extension onto the cable.  Stand with your feet hips width apart, your elbows tucked into your side, exhale, and pull the bar down.  Slowly return the bar to your starting position.</p>
<p>Repeat for 3 x&#8217;s 12.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br />
</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Crunch</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Lie on your back, bend your knees and bring your heels off the ground.  Place your hands underneath your head, and crunch up with your <a class="zem_slink" title="Chin-up" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chin-up">chin up</a> toward the ceiling. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Repeat for 2 x&#8217;s 15.</p>
<p><strong><em>Warning: If you begin to feel low back pain stop immediately.</em></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
