      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1 class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;"><a href="http://www.healthandfitsolutions.com" target="_blank">Health and Fit Solutions.com <span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;"> </span></a></span> </h1>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"></strong> </p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">Home Exercise Program for: </strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Robin</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Lateral Step</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand with your feet about hips width apart, step to your R leading with your R foot.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Squat, evenly distributing your weight through both of your heels, hold for one second, then step back.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Alternate and step to your L.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Upright Row </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand in a squat position; your feet about hips width apart, and your knees supple.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Position your hands to face your body, and hold onto 5 lbs in each hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Bend your elbows and bring the dumbbells up to your chest just above your bust.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Be sure you pull your shoulder blades down toward the ground as you pull the weights up to your chest.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Hold for 1 second, then slowly lower the weights down to return to your starting position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Lat Pull Down</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">On the lat pull down machine, sit facing the weight stack and place your hands close to each other.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Load the machined with 40lbs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Exhale and pull the bar down to your chest by lower your elbows, inhale and slowly release the bar, making sure to pull your shoulder blades down toward your back pocket (ensuring your shoulders do not come up).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Chest Press Machine</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Lie on your back with the bench flat on the chest press machine, or sit up on a chair style machine.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Load the machine with 20lbs and position the handles of the machine so that it is perpendicular to your shoulder.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Keeping your back flat (it may be easier to do so if your feet are on the bench), exhale and push the bar up above your chest.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Slowly lower down to starting position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;"><br style="page-break-before: always;" /></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Overhead Shoulder Press (Machine)</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Position the machine with the shoulder press at your shoulder height and load it with 10lbs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Sit with your back flat against the chair, exhale and press up until your shoulders and elbows are extended (though they still have a slight bend).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Slowly lower the press down.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></em></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">OR </span></span></em></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Overhead Shoulder Press</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Sitting on a bench, holding 5lb dumbbells in each hand, raise your elbows and palms forward to shoulder height.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Exhale, then push the weights up and in, over your head.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Slowly lower them to the starting position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Sit tall so that your back remains flat in a stable and safe position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Do not arch your back.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">    </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Sit Back</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand in front of a bench or tall step with your feet about hips width apart.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Keeping your back flat, push your butt back, and nearly sit down onto the step (act like you are going to sit on the step, but don’t).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Hold for a brief second, and then push your weight through your heels as you stand to the starting position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Hammer Curl</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand in a squatted position, knees bent, butt out, and chest forward, holding onto 8lb dumbbells in each hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Keep your arms close to your body and palms facing in.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Bend your elbows and bring the weights to your shoulders (keeping your elbows tucked in).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 12<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"></strong></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Machine Triceps Extension with a Bar</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Load the cable column machine with 35lbs, and attach the bar extension onto the cable.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Stand with your feet hips width apart, your elbows tucked into your side, exhale, and pull the bar down.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Slowly return your the rope to your starting position.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Biceps Curl</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand in a Stand in a squatted position, knees bent, butt out, and chest forward.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">    </span>Palms forward, holding onto 5lbs, press your elbows into your stomach, bend your elbows to your shoulders.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 12.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Side Bends</span></span></span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Stand with your feet about hips width apart holding onto an 8lb dumbbell in your R hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span>Place your L hand on your head; bend your chest to your R then to your L.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;">Repeat for 3 x’s 15, and then alternate.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"> </p>
