      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> </p>
<p>I never really liked asparagus.  It was one of those funny veggies that when cooked gets this funky slimy texture.  Gross!  <img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-111" title="asp-1" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/asp-1-300x225.jpg" alt="asp-1" width="300" height="225" /></p>
<p>One of the biggest issues when it comes to vegetables is to know how to cook them. </p>
<p>Here is a very simple recipe and  had my husband looking for more.  If you know my husband&#8230;.he NEVER looks for more vegetables!!!  NEVER!</p>
<p>Spray your non-stick grill pan with some pam.</p>
<p>Trim the hard woody looking bits off the bottom of the asparagus</p>
<p>I placed the asparagus on a plate, and drizzled a little bit of <strong>olive oil</strong> all over them.  Get your hands in there and mix it all up so each spear is very lightly coated.  Place in your pan and take a pinch of <strong>sea salt</strong> and sprinkle it all over.</p>
<p>Put the pan on a hot grill and grill for about 3 min or until they are hot through out and bright green.</p>
<p>Done! Delish!</p>
