Similar Posts from Food and Sugar Addiction:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/food-and-sugar-addiction/dealing-fatchick/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Dealing With My Inner Fatchick!'&gt;Dealing With My Inner Fatchick!&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;    Dealing With My Inner Fatchick!     The crazy...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/food-and-sugar-addiction/mothers-daughters/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Mothers and Daughters'&gt;Mothers and Daughters&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;. I have struggled with my weight and sugar cravings...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/food-and-sugar-addiction/control-sugar-cravings/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Control for Sugar Cravings!'&gt;Control for Sugar Cravings!&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt;Sometimes we think we are going mad.  The sugar cravings...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/food-and-sugar-addiction/Food_and_Sugar_Addiction-Food_Addiction.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> </p>
<p>Last night&#8217;s supper was steel head trout, Caesar salad and a baked potato.  Now since I had been having issues with cravings and not getting enough food, I thought I&#8217;d try the potato.  In my head I said to myself, &#8220;eat the fish and salad first.  If you still want more, have the potato.&#8221;  Well of course that isn&#8217;t exactly how it all played thru. <img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-103" title="fish" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/fish-300x199.jpg" alt="fish" width="300" height="199" /></p>
<p>I ate the fish first because it was absolutely delicious! I blobbed a heaping tsp of lite sour cream with fresh chopped chives from the garden ontop of my potato.  Leaving the salad in the bowl. </p>
<p><strong>Addiction</strong> and habits are very hard to break.  After finishing my fish, I went right for the potato.  Why?  I really don&#8217;t know.  Knowing I should be eating the salad first before diving into the potato, I started on the green stuff. </p>
<p>Here is the really cool part.  After practising the Beck way of living, I recognize when I am full.  Not just stuffed, but when my stomach is satisfied.  I had finished 1/2 my small potato, and still had about 1/4 of my salad left to eat.  I left it all. </p>
<p>This is really hard for someone like me.  It is hard to rationalize in my brain that throwing it out is not wasting it.  Because if I ate it, it would still go to waist.  See my point? </p>
<p>Last night brought on what I call &#8220;ghost hunger&#8221;.  I have eaten maybe 2.5 hours before.  A good balanced meal&#8230;and the big clue that it was still in my belly?  I was still burping fish and garlicy salad! So I KNEW I really wasn&#8217;t hungry.  What was it?  I really don&#8217;t know.  I had a glass of water, then made my herbal tea, and everything seemed to be fine. </p>
<p>In the past I would have taken that &#8220;ghost hunger&#8221; and fed it with potato chips, chocolate, wine&#8230;what ever I could get my hands on.  When you are trying to train yourself to recognize true hunger, this one can be a bit tricky.</p>
<p>Just remember that &#8220;hunger is NOT an emergency&#8221;</p>
