      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Because I said so!</strong> (That&#8217;s the only reason you need!) Ha! Right! Wish it was that simple!</p>
<p>One of the benefits of being a yo-yo dieter I have seen what I look like at different weights. Not just at different weights, but also the same weight several years apart. (did that make sense?)</p>
<p>Here is a visual. The first photo was taken about 11 yrs ago in Florida. My first ever visit to the ocean. The second photo was take about 4 yrs ago. I finally got back down to 195. The most exercise I did back then was walking. As good as that was, it wasn&#8217;t enough. These pants are size 20.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-47" title="in-the-ocean1" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/in-the-ocean1-300x231.jpg" alt="in-the-ocean1" width="300" height="231" /></p>
<p>This was after loosing what I put back on, and started the Body For Life workout program. No question in my mind which photo looks better. 195 here as well. Yes I know I&#8217;ve got a little person stuck in front of me hiding me. (but wasn&#8217;t that the point when the photo was taken?) These jeans are a size 16.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-48" title="me-and-my-girl1" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/me-and-my-girl1-195x300.jpg" alt="me-and-my-girl1" width="195" height="300" /></p>
<p>No matter what you do for exercise, be sure to incorporate some sort of resistance training. It builds great bones, packs your body a bit tighter (we all need that don&#8217;t we ladies?) and you don&#8217;t have to run to &#8220;strong-oh&#8221; hubby to open jars for you!</p>
<p>The book I used for resistance training was <strong><a href="http://astore.amazon.com/buffagraph0b-20/detail/0060193395">Body For Life</a></strong>, by Bill Phillips. I love this book for the excellent guide it offered me. I still like to go back to it when Im starting over and need to get back to it.</p>
<p>A bit of a warning tho. If you are a <strong>food or sugar addict</strong>, I suggest you do NOT follow his food plan. It worked well enough for me, until I got to the &#8220;free&#8221; day. Which turned into a free-for-all. Ultimately derailed me. I also do not like having to think about food all the time. I just want to eat what Ive planned, then wait until the next feeding time. For me it has to be that way&#8230;..otherwise I&#8217;ll eat all day.</p>
<p>Folks if you want to comment on this, please go over to the &#8220;about&#8221; page and post comments there, with the title of this post in your comments so I will know what you are commenting on. I have to do this until I can figure out what I did to the comments on this page. They dissappeared! (yah I did it, I just don&#8217;t know how to fix it)</p>
