      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="attachment_17" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 310px"><img class="size-medium wp-image-17" title="December/08" src="http://www.foodandsugaraddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/pict04441-300x225.jpg" alt="Me " width="300" height="225" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Me </p></div>
<p>I recommitted today! April 19, 2009.</p>
<p>I did what I should not have done last night. I am one of those “all or nothing” type people. Something I really need to learn to rein in.</p>
<p>I ate to feel the emotions. Did it feel good? Yes at the time it did. Does it feel good now? No, I still have a sugar headache.</p>
<p>Some of the things that happen to me when I’m not eating properly:<br />
(or eating too much crappy nutritionally void foods)</p>
<p>1. my hair falls out by the handfuls (its looking pretty scraggly right now)<br />
2. my skin gets irritated and my eczema flairs up<br />
3. I get fat (duh!) You’d think I had this one figured out<br />
4. my feet hurt<br />
5. I get winded much faster<br />
6. I have almost constant headaches<br />
7. crave more sugar<br />
8. crave more flour based items (donuts, bread, pasta etc)<br />
9. my teeth bother me (strange I know)</p>
<p>When I eat properly<br />
1. I have beautiful glossy curly hair<br />
2. my skin isn’t bothering me at all<br />
3. I loose weight<br />
4. my feet do not hurt<br />
5. I can walk the treadmill or neighbourhood without sucking wind!<br />
6. a bottle of ibuprofen lasts for months<br />
7. I don’t crave anything!<br />
8. my teeth are just fine</p>
<p>Ok…so what’s the problem you might ask? Ha! I’ve been trying to figure that out for years!</p>
<p>Stay tuned….it’s coming to me.</p>
